solutions.content:
# Approach
Using **s.find(words[i])** function which returns the index of words[i] if it is present in the string s , and to check whether words[i] occurs as a prefix use **s.find(words[i])==0**  ( since prefix always occurs at index 0).

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countPrefixes(vector<string>& words, string s) {

      int countPrefix = 0;

      for(int i=0;i<words.size();++i){
          if(s.find(words[i])!=string::npos && s.find(words[i])==0){
              countPrefix++;
          }
      }  
      return countPrefix;
    }
};
```

