considering {1210}

    HASHMAP :

    {
        0:1
        1:2
        2:3
    }

    index : 0 1 2 3
    number: 1 2 1 0

    according to the question,

    num[i] should be equal to frequency of index i

    let x = num.charAt(i)
    convert character to integer using -
    int a = x - '0';

    thus, if(a != frequency of a) i.e if(a != map.get(i)) return false;


    but to avoid null pointer exception, we must check if the hashmap contains all indices or not, if it doesnt, then num[i] must be 0 as in this case,

index 3 is not in hashmap {
        0:1
        1:2
        2:3
    }

so , if it doesnot contain in hashmap (! map.containsKey(i))

then check if num[i] must be 0, else return false;,
if it is 0, then continue

# Time Complexity - O(n)
# Space Complexity - O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public boolean digitCount(String num) {

        //creating an integer - integer hashmap

        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        for(int i = 0; i < num.length(); i++)
        {
            char x = num.charAt(i);

            int a = x - '0'; // to create character to integer

            if(map.containsKey(a))
                map.put(a,map.get(a)+1);

            else
                map.put(a,1);

        }

        for(int i = 0; i<num.length(); i++)
        {

            // to avoid nullPointerException

            if(!map.containsKey(i))
            {
                if(num.charAt(i)!='0') //it must be 0, else false
                    return false;
                else //if it is 0, then continue
                    continue;
            }
            char x = num.charAt(i); //let num[i] = x
            int a = x - '0'; //convert x to int
            if(a!=map.get(i)) //check if its equal to frequency
                return false;

        }

        return true;
    }
}
```

