# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
After looking at the question the intuition that comes to my mind is to sort the potions vector and corresponding to every spell value will find the index of the minimum value in the potions vector whose value becomes equal to or greater than the success value given to us.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We have to find how many potions are there whose multiplication with that particular spell value is greater than or equal to the success value given to us. 

The first thing that comes to mind is to sort that potions vector. Now try to find the index of that minimum value in the potions vector whose multiplication with the particular spell value becomes equal to or surpasses the success value given to us. (Ofcourse the values after that particular index will satisfy the criteria because we already sorted the vector in the first place.)

We will use lower_bound function here, which returns the iterator of that particular value if that particular value is present in the vector. And if that particular value is not present in the vector it will give us the iterator of the value which is greater than that value. We'll then subtract this iterator from the base iterator(potions.begin()) to find the index. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
The for loop is running for n times where n = spells.size() and the lower bound function takes logN time where N - potions.size().

So the TOTAL TIME COMPLEXITY IS O(nlogN);


- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We are using space to store the ans only. so the space complexity O(n) where n = spells.size()

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> successfulPairs(vector<int>& spells, vector<int>& potions, long long success) {

        vector<int> ans;
        sort(potions.begin(),potions.end());


        for(int i=0; i<spells.size(); i++){
            long long value = ceil(success/(spells[i]*1.0));
            auto it = lower_bound(potions.begin(),potions.end(),value);

            int res = 0;

            if(it!=potions.end()){
                int ind = it-potions.begin();
                res += potions.size()-ind;
                ans.push_back(res);
            }
            else{
                ans.push_back(0);
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

