![Spiral Matrix IV stats.jpg](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/a5faf6ef-1ff2-453b-a93c-cab8541028ec_1691608455.8859637.jpeg)


# Approach
- We declare a 2D matrix of size m * n initialized with -1.
- Set limits ```left=0``` , ```right=n-1```, ```up=1``` and ```down=m-1```
- First row is (u=0) is done, hence u=0+1=1
- " ALL LIMITS ARE INCLUSIVE"
- Go till ```head!=NULL```
- go right, then update r limit and increase i at the end
- go down, then update d limit and decrease j at the end
- go right, then update r limit and increase i at the end
- go right, then update r limit and increase i at the end

# ! ! - -  Note - - ! !
We don't need to check if ```ans[i][j]==1``` as we are declaring limits and updating the limits, hence checking for -1 is not required.

# Complexity
- Time complexity : O(number of nodes) = O( m * n )

- Space complexity : O(number of nodes) = O( m * n )

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> spiralMatrix(int m, int n, ListNode* head) {
        vector<vector<int>> ans(m, vector<int>(n, -1)); // initialize matrix with -1
        int i=0, j=0; // declare traversal indices

        // set limits left , right, up and down " ALL ARE INCLUSIVE"
        int l=0, r=n-1, u=1, d=m-1; // first row (u=0) is done, hence u=1

        while(head){ // go on till head is not NULL

            while(head && j<=r){ // go right in the same row (i, j++)
                ans[i][j]=head->val;
                head=head->next;
                if(j==r) {
                    r--;
                    i++; // go clockwise
                    break;
                }
                else j++; // continue in the same row
            }
            while(head && i<=d){ // go down in the same column (i++, j)
                ans[i][j]=head->val;
                head=head->next;
                if(i==d) {
                    d--;
                    j--; // go clockwise
                    break;
                }
                else i++; // continue in the same column
            }
            while(head && j>=l){ // go left in the same row (i, j--)
                ans[i][j]=head->val;
                head=head->next;
                if(j==l) {
                    l++;
                    i--; // go clockwise
                    break;
                }
                else j--; // continue in the same row
            }
            while(head && i>=u) { // go up in the same column (i++, j)
                ans[i][j]=head->val;
                head=head->next;
                if(i==u) {
                    u++;
                    j++; // go clockwise
                    break;
                }
                else i--; // continue in the same column
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

