solutions.content:
**Problem** states that we need to convert **start** string to **target** string by moving 'L' to left and 'R' to right in **Start**.

**3 observations to make here** - 

**1. Start string can only be converted into Target string if and only if relative order of 'L' and 'R' is equal.**

Example - 
Start = "-L-R--L-R"
Target = "--R--L--LR"

Now here we can see that order of LR in start is -> LRLR but in Target is RLLR so it can never be converted into Target because L and R can never cross each other.


**2. Now relative order being same doesn't concludes that Start can always be converted to the Target.**

Example - 
Start = "L-RRL"
Target = "LR-RL"

Here relative order is same but to convert Start to Target we will need to move R to Left which is not Possible.

Now here comes our 3rd Observation

**3. That although relative order is same but if need to move any R of start to Left or any L to right then also Start can never be converted into Target.**

Now how to check for this??

To check (suppose for R in the above example) this we will store indexes of R from both Start and Target in say arrays - r1 (For start) and r2 for(Target) and check for every i in r1  r1[i]<=r2[i].
Similarly for L l1[i]>=l2[i]


**DRY RUN -**

Start = "L - R R L"
Target="L R - R L"

**now here relative order is same** , so may be start can be converted to Target

now r1 and r2 will look like this - 

r1 = [2,3]  r2 = [1,3]

so now for i=0 r1[i]>r2[i] which simply denotes that to convert the S->T we need to move R at index 2 in Start in Left direction to make it match with R at index 1 in Target and which is not possible , Hence we cannot convert S->T.


Code - 

```
class Solution {
public:
    bool static seqSame(string s1,string s2){
        string a,b;
        for(auto it : s1) if(it!='_') a+=it;
        for(auto it : s2) if(it!='_') b+=it;
        return a==b;
    }
    bool canChange(string start, string target) {
        int n = start.length();
        if(!seqSame(start,target)) return false;
        vector<int> l1,l2,r1,r2;

        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            if(start[i]=='L') l1.push_back(i);
            if(start[i]=='R') r1.push_back(i);
            if(target[i]=='L') l2.push_back(i);
            if(target[i]=='R') r2.push_back(i);
        }

        for(int i=0 ; i<l1.size() ; i++) if(l1[i]<l2[i]) return false;
        for(int i=0 ; i<r1.size() ; i++) if(r1[i]>r2[i]) return false;

        return true;
    }
};
```

