If <code>target</code> can be obtained from <code>start</code>, then
<ol>
	<li>After we remove all <code>'_'</code> from them, the corresponding string <code>s1</code> and <code>s2</code> should be the same; 
	<li>Besides, since <code>'R'</code> can only be moved to the right, the number of <code>'_'</code> before the <code>i<sub>th</sub></code> <code>'R'</code> in <code>target</code> should be more than the corresponding <code>'R'</code> in <code>start</code>;  
	<li>Similarly,  the number of <code>'_'</code> after the <code>i<sub>th</sub></code> <code>'L'</code> in <code>target</code> should be more than the corresponding <code>'L'</code> in <code>start</code>;
</ol>

