# Intuition
Just make sure L and R can move as needed.

# Approach
- Make sure that we still have R to move forward but L comes in the way e.g. S : "RL...", T : "_?..."

Also not possible if either
1. we have extra L (in source) which cant be moved to left. e.g. S : "L...", T : "_..."
2. we dont have enough R (in source) that can be moved to right. e.g. S : "_...", T : "R..."
3. we have R to move right, and L to move left at the same time. e.g. "R...", T : "L..."

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool canChange(string start, string target) {
        int n = start.size();
        int r = 0, l = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            if (start[i] == 'L')
                ++l;
            if (start[i] == 'R')
                ++r;

            // make sure that we still have R to move forward but L comes in between e.g. S : "RL...", T : "_?..."
            if (l != 0 && r != 0) 
                return false;

            if (target[i] == 'L')
                --l;
            if (target[i] == 'R')
                --r;

            // not possible if
            // 1. we have extra L (in source) which cant be moved to left. e.g. S : "L...", T : "_..."
            // 2. we dont have enough R (in source) that can be moved to right. e.g. S : "_...", T : "R..."
            // 3. we have R to move right, and L to move left at the same time. e.g. "R...", T : "L..."
            if (l > 0 || r < 0 || (l != 0 && r != 0))
                return false;
        }
        return (l == 0) && (r == 0);
    }
};
```

