# Intuition

We keep track of positions with 2 pointers. Pointers move until finding L or R, and then we expext both of them to be pointing the same character. Additionally, for L, ptr1 must be >= ptr2 otherwise it is invalid as we cant move the L to right side. Similary for the char R, ptr1 <= ptr2

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public boolean canChange(String start, String target) {
        int n = start.length();
        if (target.length() != n) return false;
        int s = 0;
        int t = 0;

        while (s < n && t < n) {
            while (s < n && start.charAt(s) == '_') s++;
            while (t < n && target.charAt(t) == '_') t++;

            if (s >= n || t >= n) break;

            if (start.charAt(s) == 'L' && target.charAt(t) == 'L') {
                if (s < t) return false;
                s++;
                t++;
            }
            else if (start.charAt(s) == 'R' && target.charAt(t) == 'R') {
                if (s > t) return false;
                s++;
                t++;
            }
            else {
                return false;
            }
        }

        while (s < n && start.charAt(s) == '_') s++;
        while (t < n && target.charAt(t) == '_') t++;

        return s == t;
    }
}
```

