The Logic:
If someone wants a detailed explanation, please go here. It is very well explained and helped me understand how to approach it and similar tasks.

First, you can observe, that `L` can be moved to the left in the string `start` and `R` to the right.

Second, you need to analyze how the valid strings should look: basically, the relative order of `R` and `L` is matter.

The order of `R` and `L` appearance in the stings. When you loop both strings, you skip `_` and the next non-`_` symbols should be the same.
Their relative positions. L in `start` should have an index larger or equal to the corresponding index of `L` in `target`. It is because L can be moved left in the `start`. A similar thing applies to `R`.
Number of `_`, `R`, and `L` should be the same. Thus I return `return i == j` at the end.
Once you understand it, the task looks much easier.

