# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
just compare both the strings and if the character does not matches than check for all three conditions i.e. the target[i] can be L, R, _.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
- O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool canChange(string s, string t) {
        int n = s.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(s[i]==t[i]) continue;
            if(t[i]=='L'){
                if(s[i]=='_'){
                    int j=i+1;
                    while(j<n and s[j]=='_') j++;
                    if(s[j]=='R' or j>=n) return false;
                    else swap(s[i],s[j]);
                }
                if(s[i]=='R') return false;
            }
            else if(t[i]=='R') return false;
            else {
                if(s[i]=='L') return false;
                if(s[i]=='R'){
                    int j=i+1;
                    while(j<n and s[j]=='R'){
                        j++;
                    }
                    if(s[j]=='L' or j>=n) return false;
                    else swap(s[i],s[j]);
                }
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```

