            else:
                subarrays += contCount * (contCount + 1) // 2
                contCount = 0

        if contCount > 0:
            subarrays += contCount * (contCount + 1) // 2

        return subarrays
```

# 99% Efficiency:
Instead of determining the subarrays like that, couldn't we just update the subarrays whenever contCount is updated?
When we encounter a 0, contCount will be 1.
So, we found a new subarray. So, add it to the subarrays count.
Then another contiguous 0 will make the contCount = 2. So, now we will add 2 to the subarrays count. Our previous code was doing the same thing. But the multiplication and division operator takes more time than the addition operation. That's why the underneath solution will be more efficient.

