# What Problem says ?
- Given an integer array `nums`, return the no. of subarrays filled with `0`.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach : Simple Iteration
- Loops through each number in the array and keeps track of the index of the last 0 that was encountered. 
- Whenever you across a new 0, calculate the number of subarrays between the last 0 and the current 0 (which is just the distance between the two indices plus one) and adds this to a running total.
- When you encounters a number that is not 0, simply move on to the next number without doing anything else.
-  Once you have gone through the entire array, return the total number of subarrays that were found to be filled with 0s.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity :
- Time complexity : O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity : O(1)
