We can observe the no. of subarrays made by specific no. of contiguous 0's follow some pattern. We can see that any subarray of 0's of length x can make x(x-1)/2 subarrays itself.
So now we just need to find all these subarrays of 0 and calculate the no. of subarrays made by them with the above formula. One more thing we also need to include all the occurances of 0's in our answer.
# Approach
