**Logic**: Number of subarrays for each contiguous sequence of 0 is `(count*(count+1))/2`
**Edge case**: The array ending with 0 needs to be considered before returning.
```
class Solution
{
    public long zeroFilledSubarray(int[] nums)
    {
        long ans = 0L, cur = 0L;
        for(int i : nums)
        {
            if(i == 0)
                cur++;
            else
            {
                ans += (long)(1L*cur*(cur+1)/2);
                cur = 0L;
            }
        }
        ans += (long)(1L*cur*(cur+1)/2); // If the array ends with 0
        return ans;
    }
}
```

