# Approach
Just use sliding window .
1.add element to window by adding element in sum.
2.shrink window if sum is going greater than 0.
3.calculate answer by the length of window of that time.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)
- Space complexity:
O(1)
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public long zeroFilledSubarray(int[] nums) {
        int s=0;
        int e=0;
        long ans=0;
        int sum=0;
        while(e<nums.length){
            sum+=nums[e];
            while(sum!=0){
                sum-=nums[s];
                s++;
            }
        ans+=e-s+1;
        e++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
